 First, let me add the two equations together to eliminate $y$. 
\begin{align*}
(5x-2y)+(3x+y)&=7+2,\\
8x-y&=9.
\end{align*}
Next, add four times the second equation to eliminate $y$ again.
\begin{align*}
5x-2y&=7,\\
4(3x+y)&=4(2),\\
17x&=15.
\end{align*}
Solving gives $x=\dfrac{15}{17}$ and $y=-\dfrac{11}{17}$. In addition, it is easy to obtain $$24x-14y=98.$$ </think> <answer> \boxed{98} </answer>

